n ratios in the world approximately 0.2 physicians per 10,000 people. Community health workers (Health Surveillance Assistants) play a critical role in bridging service gaps.\n\n## Services {#services}\n\nMalawian health facilities deliver outpatient care, malaria prevention (including insecticide-treated nets distribution), diagnosis and treatment, maternal and neonatal health, HIV/AIDS services including ART and PMTCT, TB treatment, immunization, and nutrition services. Malaria, respiratory infections, and diarrhoeal diseases are the most common reasons for facility visits.\n\n## Data Download {#data-download}\n\nDownload facilities dataset here:\n\n-   [CSV](../data/Malawi/malawi_standardized.csv)\\\n<!--   [JSON](../data/tanzania/hf_demographics.json)-->\n-   [RDS](../data/Malawi/malawi_standardized.rds)\n",
